This is a known Android platform change — `AdjustResize` was deprecated in API 30+. In .NET MAUI 8+, the framework handles this via **`KeyboardAutoManagerScroll`**, which is enabled by default.

**If it's not working for your layout, try these steps:**

### 1. Wrap your page content in a `ScrollView`
`KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` needs a scrollable container:

```xml
<ContentPage>
  <Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <ScrollView Grid.Row="0">
      <!-- Chat messages -->
      <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" />
    </ScrollView>

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
      <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
      <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
  </Grid>
</ContentPage>
```

### 2. If auto-scroll misbehaves, disable it and handle insets manually
In your `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    // Disable MAUI's auto-scroll if it conflicts
    KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();

    // Use modern edge-to-edge inset handling
    WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);
    Window!.SetSoftInputMode(SoftInput.AdjustNothing);

    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window.DecorView, new InsetsListener());
}

private class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        // Push content up by the keyboard height
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, imeInsets.Bottom);
        return insets;
    }
}
```

### 3. Alternatively, just switch to `AdjustPan`
The simplest fix — Android pans the window so the focused `Entry` stays visible:

```csharp
// In MainActivity.cs OnCreate:
Window!.SetSoftInputMode(SoftInput.AdjustPan);
```

**Summary:** Try `AdjustPan` first (option 3) — it's one line. If you need more control over the layout shift, use the `WindowInsets` listener approach (option 2).
